icID=8558.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Hey all, <br>
<br>
I need some opinions about where to assign my 30 points. I'm going to be starting up a new High Elf mage (untwinked). Should I just follow my common sense and put all 30 into Intelligence? or should I distribute to STA since they have such a low score? HPs are fairly important now since there are INT items readily available, I assume? How did you assign your points? <br>
<br>
Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 567<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 5:05:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Can only put 25 points into one stat.<br>
<br>
My recommendations:<br>
All races: 25INT 5STR <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2742<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 6:33:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Before <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoP</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I would have not emphasized intelligence so much, but with the caps lifted, it helps post-60.  Strength helps you carry more loot, which is good, especially if you are alone on the server with no twinkage.  Make sure your agility is at least 75, and don't worry beyond that.  Stamina matters not enough.<br>
<br>
Basically, I agree with the first respondant now: INT, then STR.  It's the only combination that makes a difference.<br>
<br>
As for myself, I actually put points into charisma, but then I started alone on the server, no twinkage, and prided myself at mining merchants and making a profit thereby.  This was before the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Opal Encrusted Steins</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which now sell for 15-50 pp each, and are not LORE.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hobiewankenobe>Hobiewankenobe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://myweb.thump.net/1363/pictures/Gonn.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 548<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 3:02:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myweb.thump.net/1363/pictures/Gonn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> I put my extra in Stamina to be honest. My Str isn't much but the sta gives you more hp in the long run. Str is also nice as suggested. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joxterthemighty>JoxterTheMighty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 3:13:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> I started as a human and made sure no stat was below 75 then dumped extra into int, I like having no real weaknesses in the stat dept <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  can always get lots of stat items later. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.compudocsonline.com/fuzzy_master_mountains.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=epicureofquellious>EpicureOfQuellious</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 4:47:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Put as many as you can into stamina   then top off intelligence. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65160&amp;resize=true" target="top">Epicure</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1672<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 5:07:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Starting out as a newbie, being able to carry stuff becomes rather important since you need to keep and sell all the loot you can find.  With high elves horrible 55 STR, I'd suggest putting some of the points into that along with INT.<br>
<br>
If you really want to play the &quot;well when I'm 60+ level&quot; game (and honestly, many don't make it that far), then STA is actually the good one to do for extra HP.  At level 60 I had plenty of weight reducing bags, so STR wasn't so much a problem anymore.  And with KEI I have max INT, so that wasn't much of a problem either.  In fact my +8 Int cloak is banked right now for my +75hp/+75mana, +resists cloak.  My +14 INT robe is banked for my +5 Int, +50hp/+50mana, +resists robe.  And so on. . .<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 797<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 5:21:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> My mage was my 3rd or 4th character that i created, but none had advanced past level 10 (back in Jan of 2000). At the time, I thought a well rounded character would be the best way to go, so I dropped 5 in str, a few in dex and agi, and a few in sta and cha. But then again, I knew absolutely nothing about the game back then. I thought the best way to twink a character was to take 10 platinum on a higher levelcharacter, and jump off of a lift in Kelethin. Then do a /consent twink command, log out, and let the twink loot the corpse. Ha, back when 10p would constitute twinking <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Keep in mind that these points your spending have the greatest impact late in your life. This is why + hp and +mana gear are so important for lowbie characters.<br>
<br>
If you're going to go untwinked, STR would be fairly important, as you can carry more loot (those heavy rusty weapons and staves), and at lower levels, it will help your melee damage. Dex will help you maximize your offensive skills.<br>
<br>
STA used to be very important for mages that would do a lot of rodding (before the nerf), or get beat on a lot. If you're not into aggro kiting, STA will have less importance.<br>
<br>
Just about any stat can be beefed up with gear later in life, so its really a question of how you intend to play your new mage that will determine where to put your points. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 57th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/24/03 5:22:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 751<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 6:51:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Eruidtes start with only 70 base agl, and there is a massive increase in ac from 70 to 75. So I did +25 int +5agl. Int helps you throughout your career in my view. Even these days my high base erudite int lets me be completely dismissive of +int items, allowing me to use some pretty strong gear without int on it.<br>
<br>
Otherwise stamina or strength are good.<br>
<br>
EDIT: just rememebred you are committed to a high elf. Well my instinct would be 25 int (espcially since they have relatively low int) and 5 str.<br>
I never understood why people play high elf magicians, but hey if it's part of your roleplaying conception, more power to you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Master Cydmab Promethean<br>
Arch Convoker of Morell Thule<br>
Fury's Edge</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A> at: 1/24/03 6:54:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=canvashan>canvashan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 7:00:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> Max out INT than Stamina.<br>
<br>
I don't really worry about carrying around loot.  You can always buy/quest weight reduction bags.  Stamina is important because of Hit Points.  Items with hitpoints are highly valued in EQ because they are worth it.  You wanna get as much Hit Points you can get and it'll save you from death from time to time.<br>
<br>
Canvashan<br>
Convoker of the Seventh Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 7:21:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8558.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Assigning points</span><hr size=1> I agree with the poster about Int and Str.<br>
<br>
Strength is always handy to have when you're trying to haul that last ounce of loot out of Crushbone so you can buy your last spell, or when you'd like to kill a few more hill giants but are so encumbered that you can't chase them down any more...<br>
<br>
On the other hand, hit points and armor class really aren't things you should have to worry about if you're playing your class right. <br>
<br>
